1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,679
2.

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:06,080
Withdraw only positive thoughts from your memory bank.

3
00:00:06,510 --> 00:00:13,039
I was closely associated several years ago in Chicago with a firm of psychological consultants.

4
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:22,400
They handled many types of cases, but mostly marriage problems and psychological adjustment situations, all dealing with mind matters.

5
00:00:22,990 --> 00:00:31,440
One afternoon, as I was talking with the head of the firm about his profession and his techniques for helping the seriously maladjusted person,

6
00:00:31,550 --> 00:00:33,120
he made this remark.

7
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:39,200
You know, there would be no need for my services if people would do just one thing.

8
00:00:39,710 --> 00:00:40,640
What's that?

9
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,000
I asked eagerly.

10
00:00:42,510 --> 00:00:43,600
Simply this.

11
00:00:43,870 --> 00:00:48,960
Destroy their negative thoughts before those thoughts become mental monsters.

12
00:00:49,310 --> 00:00:57,120
Most individuals I try to help," he continued, are operating their own private museum of mental horror.

13
00:00:57,310 --> 00:01:02,480
Many marriage difficulties, for example, involve the honeymoon monster.

14
00:01:02,590 --> 00:01:08,159
The honeymoon wasn't as satisfactory as one or both of the marriage partners had hoped,

15
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:17,199
but instead of burying the memory, they reflected on it hundreds of times until it was a giant obstacle to successful marital relationships.

16
00:01:17,470 --> 00:01:20,959
They come to me as much as five or ten years later.

17
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:25,760
Usually, of course, my clients don't see where their trouble lies.

18
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:33,999
It's my job to uncover and explain the source of their difficulty to them and help them to see what a triviality it really is.

19
00:01:34,429 --> 00:01:41,520
A person can make a mental monster out of almost any unpleasant happening, my psychologist friend went on.

20
00:01:41,790 --> 00:01:49,040
a job failure, a jilted romance, a bad investment, disappointment in the behavior of a teenage child.

21
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:53,679
These are common monsters I have to help troubled people destroy.

22
00:01:54,270 --> 00:02:02,320
It is clear that any negative thought, if fertilized with repeated recall, can develop into a real mind monster,

23
00:02:02,429 --> 00:02:07,840
breaking down confidence and paving the way to serious psychological difficulties.

24
00:02:08,429 --> 00:02:24,400
In an article in Cosmopolitan magazine, The Drive Toward Self-Destruction, Alice Mulcahy pointed out that upward of 30,000 Americans commit suicide each year and another 100,000 attempt to take their own lives.

